# Hardware Design Standard

Design for **diagnostics** and **serviceability**:

- Modular boards (Logic / Power / Radio); Gen2 swaps Power only where approved.
- Test points: SWD, CAN, SPI, sense, NTC — without unsafe high-current exposure on production.
- Approved connector families (Deutsch DTM/DT/DTP) unless EDL changes policy.
- Separate power/logic domains; documented ground strategy and thermal paths.
- High-current: verified copper, busbars, connector derating — not headline amp ratings alone.

Create KiCad/schematics **only when explicitly requested**.

Refs: `docs/002_DCC_Hardware.md`, `docs/007_Component_Selection.md`, `drivecore-engineering.mdc` §10.
